  "prompt": "What does President Duterte think of Donald Trump?",
  "response": "Rodrigo Duterte, the former President of the Philippines, has expressed various opinions about former U.S. President Donald Trump over the years. Initially, Duterte seemed to have a favorable view of Trump, particularly because of Trump's non-interventionist stance and comments about improving U.S.-Philippines relations. Duterte appreciated Trump's approach to governance and even stated that he felt they were alike in their candid and unconventional political style.\n\nHowever, as with many political relationships, Duterte's stance has sometimes shifted based on specific issues or circumstances. Overall, Duterte's remarks have generally leaned towards a positive regard for Trump while underlining commonalities in their personalities and leadership approaches.",
